{"type":"message","id":"3e8b869c","parentId":"bb93cef4","timestamp":"2026-03-06T02:00:40.499Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a human message asking about the status of a feature implementation. According to my AGENTS.md routing rules:\n\n1. This is a question about a product/feature - NOT something I should answer myself\n2. The MANDATORY GATE says I must route this via Claude Code to classify and route\n\nLet me check the disambiguation rules:\n- \"what's the status of [feature]?\" -> ogedei (not kublai)\n\nFrom the routing table:\n- Development: temujin - code, build, fix, deploy, design, architect, payment, protocol, SDK\n- Operations: ogedei - monitor, alert, status check, backup, incident, health, feature status\n\nThis is a \"status check\" of a feature, which goes to ogedei. But the AGENTS.md says I should NOT make this determination myself - I should spawn Claude Code to classify and route.\n\nThe MANDATORY GATE is clear:\n\"For EVERY human message, unless it is ONLY about Kurultai agent status, routing config, or agent health:\n1. Immediately spawn Claude Code to classify and route\"\n\nThis question is about x402 pay-as-you-go implementation status - it's NOT about Kurultai agent status, routing config, or agent health. So I must spawn Claude Code to route it.\n\nI need to use sessions_spawn with runtime: \"acp\", agentId: \"claude\", mode: \"run\" and include the routing task with the human message.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_72386aabcb2241499610893d","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"ROUTING TASK — Read ~/.openclaw/skills/kurultai-router/SKILL.md and follow its decision tree to classify this human message. Determine the target agent. Then create the task by running: python3 ~/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/task_intake.py --title '<concise summary>' --body '<full message with context>' --agent <agent_id> --priority normal --source gateway-router. Print the agent name a